11, 2 (2004), 104–112. DOI: 10.1197/jamia.M1471</cite> [<a href="https://doi.org/10.1197/jamia.M1471" class="usa-link usa-link--external" data-ga-action="click_feat_suppl" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">DOI</a>] [<a href="/articles/PMC353015/" class="usa-link">PMC free article</a>] [<a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/14633936/" class="usa-link">PubMed</a>] [<a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?journal=Journal%20of%20the%20American%20Medical%20Informatics%20Association:%20JAMIA&amp;title=Some%20unintended%20consequences%20of%20information%20technology%20in%20health%20care:%20the%20nature%20of%20patient%20care%20information%20system-related%20errors&amp;author=Joan%20S.%20Ash&amp;author=Marc%20Berg&amp;author=Enrico%20Coiera&amp;volume=11&amp;issue=2&amp;publication_year=2004&amp;pages=104-112&amp;pmid=14633936&amp;doi=10.1197/jamia.M1471&amp;" class="usa-link usa-link--external" data-ga-action="click_feat_suppl" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Scholar</a>]</li>
